pr_body:
Json objects are ordered, python dicts are not, which will cause code depending on ordering eg. 
{
 'name': 'joe',
 'surname': 'bloggs'
}

to output surname first if it just iterated through the key/values.

@travistruett @wesokes 

This adds a duration field type that can convert durations expressed as `[hh:]mm:ss` to the appropriate amount of time in terms of seconds. It also fails-over to parsing as a regular number. 

In the fulcrum form, I'll add a duration type field which will create a duration type metric using Travis' formatting change, and this field type for parsing.
